values.name: Description
values.value: An agreed settlement between Warner Chappell and the contracting party, such as that arising from an audit claim.  Settlement Advances are not typically recoupable but they could be.

values.name: Description
values.value: Defined either as part of the original contract or a contract amendment.  A Contractual Advance may have additional conditions as to when it shall be paid (e.g., on contract execution, on exercise of an option, on completion of MDRC).

values.name: Description
values.value: An advance that is not defined in the contract, and does not warrant a contract amendment, but is agreed to by Warner Chappell.  A typical example of a Non-Contractual Advance is when an established Contracting Party has a solid revenue stream and needs money.  S/he can request a Non-Contractual Advance, which is typically expected to be recouped.

values.name: Description
values.value: Provides for a party, who may or may not be the contracting party, to receive a portion of WCM's Income. This income entitlement is typically based on WCM earning a certain amount of NPS. Common on Purchase Deals in the US and on many Deals in Italy (referred to as MPR Advance).

templates.name: Code
templates.description: Unique identifier for the End Rule Term Type

templates.name: Term Name
templates.description: A succinct title that populates the menus on the End Rule interface, e.g. "MDRC Complete."

templates.name: End Date Type UI Copy
templates.description: This field is optional and, if defined, this alternate copy displays as the menu selection for "End Date Type" instead of the Condition Name. Example: The Term Name "Balance Repaid" can be expressed alternately as "Repayment Date," so that the End Rule the user is building reads better.

templates.name: Term Type
templates.description: Identifies the type of Term being added to the system: Date, Numeric, Percent, or Boolean (e.g., Y/N)

templates.name: Percentage
templates.description: Select whether the Term requires a percentage.

templates.name: Date
templates.description: Select whether the Term requires a date. If so, then Variable Left Percent and Variable Left Amount should be "not applicable" for this Term.

templates.name: Amount
templates.description: Select whether the Term requires an amount.

templates.name: Notice
templates.description: Select "yes" if the contract specifies that the Condition is only fulfilled if the party provides notice. Example: MDRC Complete "with notice."

templates.name: Applicable to Contract Period End
templates.description: Select if this Condition is applicable in the context of the Contract Period ending and its accompanying rules.

templates.name: Applicable to Retention End
templates.description: Select if this Condition is applicable in the context of Retention Period ending and its accompanying rules.

templates.name: Applicable to Variable Left
templates.description: Determines whether the Condition is a valid selection for the Variable Left.

templates.name: Applicable to Variable Right
templates.description: Determines whether the Condition is a valid selection for the Variable Right.

templates.name: Applicable to End Date Type
templates.description: Determines whether the Condition is a valid selection as an End Date Type.

templates.name: Offset
templates.description: Select "yes," if the contract specifies as part of the Condition that once the End Date Type is fulfilled, then a period of time must pass. Example: "30 days after receipt of notice of completion"

templates.name: Attribute Left One Is Required
templates.description: Select whether the Term's Attribute requires a choice�this choice will be between percent or amount (e.g. Recouped).

templates.name: End Type Accounting Period End
templates.description: Select "yes," if the contract specifies as part of the Condition that the End Date Type is only fulfilled at the end of the accounting period. Example: "end of semi-accounting period during which recoupment occurs".
